article.headline: Northwestern State 84, Henderson State 64
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. (AP) -- Luke Rogers scored 16 points to lead four Northwestern State players in double figures en route to an 84-64 victory Wednesday over Henderson State. The Demons (2-2), who led 34-32 at the half, outscored the Reddies (2-1) 50-32 while forcing 29 second half turnovers. In all, the Reddies committed 33 turnovers that led to 35 Northwestern State points. The two teams kept it close in the first half with 11 lead changes and three tie scores. Henderson State led by seven points, 20-13, with 10:10 to play in the half before the Demons put together a 12-4 run to grab a 25-24 lead with 5:24 to play. A 3-pointer by Eric Woods with 10 seconds left put the Demons up 34-32 going into the break. Northwestern State used a 16-6 run in the first five minutes of the second half to open up a 50-38 lead. A 3-pointer by Keithan Hancock gave the Demons a 56-42 lead with 10:57 to play, but the Demons then strung together a 13-0 run capped off by back-to-back treys by Kennan Jones and Trey Gilder to make it 69-42 with 7:52 to play. The Reddies were able to stop the bleeding with a mild run late in the game, but Colby Bargeman and Hancock answered with 3-pointers while Damon Jones topped off the Demon scoring with a trey. Bargeman finished the night with 13 points, while Gilder added 12 and Jermaine Spencer had 10. Ryan Price led Henderson State with 16 points while Antoine Vinson added 14.
